🛠 Technical Hierarchy Implementation
The system defines the weight of truth through exact code mechanisms, where program logic is strictly subordinated to the authority hierarchy.

L1 Consortium (1.0 / 100%): The highest ethical and control body. It defines the "Golden Standard." L1 commands manually "anchor" the truth using extreme fixation of the n parameter, creating immunity against future fluctuations.

L0 Owner / Parent (0.8 / 80%): The executive power of the node. L0 sets accreditation parameters, filter strictness, and manages the teacher database. It holds the right of "Hard Input" to override disputed data.

L3 Truth System (Truth Scaling): The active core that calculates the Truth Index (IP), identifies deviations, and reports them to the disputed records database for L0. It contains the Semantic Bypass, which filters inputs and triggers the "Curious Child" process.

L2 Teacher / Expert (0.5 / 50%): An accredited node whose weight in the system is dynamic. L2 consults the accreditation database (managed by L0), and its influence on IP changes based on its history of alignment with reality.

